tracks.description: Day 1. California. The route was the same as I made a year ago but in this time it was much faster and easier. Nothing special in the day, mostly flat. At the destination point a campground in Brannan Island State Park has suddenly been closed and  I used a road shoulder for camping.

tracks.title: Daily ride 2022-05-05 #532
tracks.description: Day 3. California. Tent. That was hard to climb to 2500m which is my personal record of altitude reached with a bicycle. It is not surprising that in the mountains were cold and windy. The wind was like a storm, I spent a lot of effort and 30 mins for setting the tent up.

tracks.title: Daily ride 2022-05-06 #533
tracks.description: Day 4. Nevada. Tent. Welcome To Nevada. High altitude, good state of roads,  and wind blowing to my back allowed me to reach a good average speed and  to ride more then 200 km. A huge advantage of Nevada is that the tent could be set up everywhere, all lands are not private (almost)
